# KAK Cup Application - Environment Configuration

# ======================
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (SQLite)
# ======================
# For local development, leave DATABASE_URL commented out to use SQLite
# SQLite database will be created at ./kakcup.db

NODE_ENV=development
SESSION_SECRET=your-secret-session-key-change-this-in-production

# Optional: Customize port (defaults to 3000)
# PORT=3000

# ======================
# PRODUCTION (PostgreSQL)
# ======================
# For production deployment, set DATABASE_URL to your PostgreSQL connection string
# The app will automatically detect and use PostgreSQL when DATABASE_URL is set

# NODE_ENV=production
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@hostname:5432/database_name
# SESSION_SECRET=your-very-secure-random-session-secret

# ======================
# Vercel Postgres Example
# ======================
# If using Vercel Postgres, the DATABASE_URL is automatically set by Vercel
# Just make sure to set SESSION_SECRET in your Vercel environment variables

# ======================
# External PostgreSQL Example (Neon, Supabase, etc.)
# ======================
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host.region.provider.com:5432/dbname?sslmode=require
# SESSION_SECRET=your-session-secret-here

# ======================
# Notes
# ======================
# - SQLite is used when DATABASE_URL is NOT set (local development)
# - PostgreSQL is used when DATABASE_URL IS set (production)
# - Sessions are stored in the database (either SQLite or PostgreSQL)
# - Run "npm run db:migrate" to initialize the database and import data
